# UI Component Guidelines

This project exclusively uses shadcn/ui components for all user interface elements. Custom UI components are strictly prohibited.

## Core Principles

1. **Only shadcn/ui components**: All UI elements must use components from shadcn/ui
2. **No custom UI components**: Never create custom buttons, inputs, cards, dialogs, or any other UI primitives
3. **Clerk integration**: Authentication UI must use shadcn/ui components with Clerk modals

## shadcn/ui Component Usage

### Installing New Components

When you need a UI component that isn't already installed:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

Common components:
- `button` - All buttons must use the shadcn Button component
- `card` - For card layouts
- `dialog` - For modals and dialogs
- `input` - For text inputs
- `form` - For form elements
- `select` - For dropdowns
- `badge` - For badges and tags
- `alert` - For alerts and notifications

### Using Existing Components

Always import shadcn components from `@/components/ui/`:

```typescript
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from '@/components/ui/card';
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';
```

Existing shadcn components in the project can be found in [src/components/ui/](mdc:src/components/ui/).

## Clerk Authentication UI

### Sign In and Sign Up Buttons

All Clerk authentication triggers must use shadcn Button components:

```typescript
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { SignInButton, SignUpButton } from '@clerk/nextjs';

// ✅ CORRECT: shadcn Button with Clerk modal
<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

<SignUpButton mode="modal">
  <Button variant="outline">Sign Up</Button>
</SignUpButton>
```

### Modal Mode Required

Always use `mode="modal"` for Clerk authentication components to launch sign-in/sign-up in a modal overlay:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Modal mode
<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

// ❌ INCORRECT: Redirect mode or no mode specified
<SignInButton>
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>
```

## What NOT to Do

- ❌ Don't create custom button components
- ❌ Don't create custom input components
- ❌ Don't create custom card components
- ❌ Don't use raw HTML elements for interactive UI (except for semantic structure)
- ❌ Don't use Clerk's default redirect mode for authentication
- ❌ Don't create custom modal/dialog components
- ❌ Don't style elements from scratch - use shadcn variants and className props

```typescript
// ❌ INCORRECT: Custom button component
function CustomButton({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return <button className="custom-styles">{children}</button>;
}

// ❌ INCORRECT: Clerk without modal mode
<SignInButton>
  <button>Sign In</button>
</SignInButton>
```

## What TO Do

- ✅ Always use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/`
- ✅ Install new shadcn components when needed with `npx shadcn@latest add [component]`
- ✅ Use shadcn Button variants (default, outline, ghost, destructive, etc.)
- ✅ Use Clerk authentication with `mode="modal"`
- ✅ Wrap Clerk components with shadcn Button components
- ✅ Leverage shadcn's built-in variants and styling props
- ✅ Use className props with Tailwind for additional styling needs

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: shadcn components with Clerk modal
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '@/components/ui/card';
import { SignInButton, SignUpButton } from '@clerk/nextjs';

export function AuthButtons() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>Welcome</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent className="flex gap-2">
        <SignInButton mode="modal">
          <Button>Sign In</Button>
        </SignInButton>
        <SignUpButton mode="modal">
          <Button variant="outline">Sign Up</Button>
        </SignUpButton>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
}
```

## Available shadcn Components

Check [components.json](mdc:components.json) for the project's shadcn configuration and [src/components/ui/](mdc:src/components/ui/) for installed components.

When implementing any UI feature, first check if a shadcn component exists for it. If you need a component that isn't installed, add it using the shadcn CLI before proceeding.

## Summary

**Every UI element must use shadcn/ui:**
1. Use shadcn Button for all buttons (including Clerk auth)
2. Use shadcn components for all interactive elements
3. Never create custom UI components
4. Always use Clerk with `mode="modal"`
5. Install missing shadcn components as needed

This ensures a consistent, accessible, and maintainable UI throughout the application.
